# SURU (suru-foss) — Code Owners
# ============================================================================
# Enforces the merge gate documented in CONTRIBUTING.md: passing CI + a
# CODEOWNER review before a protected branch can merge. For this to take effect,
# enable Settings → Branches → (main, develop) → "Require review from Code Owners".
#
# Replace @cybrd0ne below with the GitHub handle(s) or team(s) that own each area.
# Matching is LAST-match-wins: more specific rules override broader ones above.
# ============================================================================

# ── Default owner (catch-all) ───────────────────────────────────────────────
*                                       @cybrd0ne

# ── Tiers ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
/tier1-perimeter/                       @cybrd0ne
/tier2-telemetry/                       @cybrd0ne
/tier3-core/                            @cybrd0ne
/tier4-operations/                      @cybrd0ne

# ── Detection content (signatures, rules, dashboards) ───────────────────────
/tier2-telemetry/suricata/              @cybrd0ne
/tier2-telemetry/zeek/                  @cybrd0ne
/tier3-core/config/opensearch/          @cybrd0ne

# ── Infrastructure as Code ──────────────────────────────────────────────────
*.tf                                    @cybrd0ne
*.tfvars                                @cybrd0ne

# ── PKI / certificates (single Root CA — highest blast radius) ──────────────
/tier4-operations/pki/                  @cybrd0ne

# ── CI / supply chain / repo governance ─────────────────────────────────────
/.github/                               @cybrd0ne
/LICENSE                                @cybrd0ne
/SECURITY.md                            @cybrd0ne
